Trichobothrial pattern: neobothriotaxic C (
Vachon, 1974
); patella with 19 external trichobothria ( 6 eb , 2 esb , 2 em , 4 est , 5 et ), and with 10 ventral trichobothria.

Variation and sexual dimorphism: female and male differ by the following characters: (
1
) females are larger, with a size ranging from 
62.5 to 64.7 mm
, in the single mature male in collection is only 
54.1 mm
(table I); (
2
) the granules on the surface of chela in male are slightly larger and more scattered than in females (fig. 
9–12
); (
3
) number of pectinal teeth (table I).
